description:
The countdown is on! On December 30, 2024, the European Union’s Deforestation-free Regulation will replace the European Timber Regulation (EUTR). This new regulation encompasses a broader range of commodities and their derivatives that contribute to deforestation, including wood, palm oil, soy, cocoa, coffee, cattle, and rubber.
The regulation imposes stringent traceability and due diligence requirements on companies involved in importing or trading commodities linked to deforestation. Compliance with the EUDR requires a comprehensive review of the supply chain, necessitating data collection, risk assessment, and submission of a due diligence statement.
At EUDR Connect 2024, you’ll have the chance to network with regulatory authorities, industry representatives, and solution experts. This event will help you develop an effective roadmap to integrate the EUDR requirements into your supply chain.
title: EUDR Connect 2024

OverviewTo advance the state of IPv6 support across the consumer electronics ecosystem, CEA and major U.S. carriers are organizing an IPv6 interoperability test event. Participants will have the opportunity to test their dual-stack (IPv4/IPv6) and IPv6 capable devices and applications with the carriers, carrier-supplied routers and IP formats that are widely deployed to millions of broadband consumers today.
Further, manufacturers will have the opportunity to test their implementation to ensure they are compliant with the recently published CEA IPv6 device profiles standard, ANSI/CEA-2048.  For more information about the CEA IPv6 Device Profiles standard, see bit.ly/1vnkvCT.
UPnP Forum will be providing their IPv6 test tool for general use at the upcoming IPv6 interop event. John Berg from CableLabs will be there with a dedicated computer to run the test, but you may want to install the test tool on your own
